Juventus, Udinese Top Serie A After Away Ties; Betis Can Extend Lead Today

-- B y   P e t e r - J o s e p h   H e g a r t y
-- 
2011-09-25T23:05:28Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-25/juventus-udinese-lead-italian-soccer-after-tying-away-games-in-serie-a.html
Juventus and Udinese share the lead
in Italian soccer’s Serie A after tying on the road.  Milos Krasic scored to give Juve a 1-1 draw at Catania
yesterday after Gonzalo Bergessio opened the scoring. Udinese’s
game at Cagliari was scoreless. Defending champion AC Milan got
its first league win of the season two days, 1-0 over Cesena,
and is in mid-table on five points.  Real Betis leads the Spanish standings with 12 points after
four straight wins and can extend its lead by beating Getafe
today. Barcelona, Levante and Sevilla have 11 points, with Real
Madrid, Malaga and Valencia on 10.  Cristiano Ronaldo got three goals two days ago in Real
Madrid’s 6-2 win over Rayo Vallecano, and  Lionel Messi  also got
a hat trick in Barca’s 5-0 victory over Atletico Madrid.  In  France , Rennes missed the chance to join Ligue 1 leaders
Lyon, Paris Saint-Germain and Toulouse on 17 points after a 1-1
home draw with  Saint Etienne  last night.  Bayern Munich  leads  Germany ’s Bundesliga by two points
following its 3-0 win over  Bayer Leverkusen  two days ago.  AZ Alkmaar  tops the Dutch standings by two points from  FC
Twente  after beating Feyenoord 2-1 at home yesterday.  To contact the reporter on this story:
